      <originalsloc id="aspace_a2aa470eabc826b96aa5ccd1f2c6ebaf">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the Canby Family Papers (MS 126).   The papers consist of diaries (1779-1831) of Samuel Canby and 24 letters to James Canby from James Asheton Bayard, Outerbridge Horsey, Louis McLane and Samuel White. Also included is a copy of the agricultural almanac for 1819 annotated by Samuel Canby.</p>
         <p>HM 240 only consist of the diaries of Samuel Canby</p>  
